name: gdbm
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "gdbm" %}
{% set version = "1.18" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: ftp://ftp.gnu.org/gnu/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha1: 0f1056ab3beb1bf09dad06f8083f2c79716a5b1b
  patches:
    # From https://github.com/spack/spack/commit/6d7daf0def6b8c432b5e79d48c96f29faf3d2db9
    - gdbm_gcc_10.patch

build:
  number: 2
  run_exports:
    # Please see ABI report
    # https://abi-laboratory.pro/index.php?view=timeline&l=gdbm
    - {{ pin_subpackage(name, max_pin='x.x') }}
  skip: True  # [win]

requirements:
  build:
    - libtool  # [unix]
    - {{ compiler('c') }}
    - make
  host:
    - readline

test:
  commands:
    - gdbm_dump --version
    - gdbm_load --version
    - gdbmtool --version

about:
  home: https://www.gnu.org.ua/software/gdbm/
  license: GPL-3.0
  license_family: GPL
  license_file: COPYING
  summary: >
    A library of database functions that use extensible hashing and works
    similar to the standard UNIX dbm functions.

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - hmaarrfk
    - jakirkham
smithy_version:
No azure token. Create a token and
put it in ~/.conda-smithy/azure.token
